<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910722-0119</DOCNO><DOCID>910722-0119.</DOCID><HL>   Boston Globe Parent   Posts 58% Decline   In 2nd-Quarter Net</HL><DATE>07/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6B</SO><CO>   AFP</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   BOSTON -- Affiliated Publications Inc., publisher of theBoston Globe, reported that second-quarter earnings fell 58%.   Net income was $3.1 million, or four cents a share,compared with $7.4 million, or 11 cents a share, a yearearlier. Revenue fell 1% to $130.9 million from $132.1million.</LP><TEXT>   The company said results continued to be affected by loweradvertising revenue at the Boston Globe caused by NewEngland's economic recession. For the quarter, operatingprofit at Affiliated's newspaper segment fell 27% to $12.2million from $16.7 million.   Affiliated said that the weak advertising environment alsoaffected its BPI Communications unit, which publishesspecialty magazines, electronic data bases and books. For thequarter, BPI had an operating loss of $2.4 million, comparedwith operating profit of $20,000 a year earlier. A &quot;majorportion&quot; of the decline was due to lower earnings of theunit's arts and design publications and operating losses atAdweek, a trade publication for the advertising industry,Affiliated said.   In the first six months, net fell 85% to $2.1 million, orthree cents a share, from $13.9 million, or 20 cents a share,a year earlier. Revenue fell 2.4% to $259.5 million from$265.8 million.</TEXT></DOC>